	iShares Gold Trust(ETF) (IAU): A Quick Guide to IAU
The IAU ETF is an effective, inexpensive way to get gold exposure

By Todd Shriber, InvestorPlace Contributor  |  Jul 18, 2017, 12:18 pm EDT



 
 









 


Popular Posts:
3 Internet ETFs to Buy For Rip-Roaring Returns3 Great ETFs to Buy for Market-Clobbering GrowthThe 3 Best Healthcare ETFs You Can Buy
Recent Posts:

3 Great ETFs to Buy for Market-Clobbering Growth
3 Internet ETFs to Buy For Rip-Roaring Returns
The 3 Best Healthcare ETFs You Can Buy


						View All Posts
					









When it comes to gold exchange-traded funds, the gold standard — no pun intended — is the SPDR Gold Shares (NYSEARCA:GLD). At the very least, GLD is the largest and most heavily traded gold ETF as well as being the preferred gold ETF for many professional traders. It also set the stage for rival iShares Gold Trust(ETF) (NYSEARCA:IAU), debuting in late 2004, and IAU quickly found its own success.

