 How To Properly Invest In An Gold ETF? What Are The Benefits | ETF Investor's Guide            ETF Investor’s Guide Menu       How To Properly Invest In An Gold ETF? What Are The Benefits Gold ETF: Benefits and Investment AdviceFor investors, Gold remains one of the hottest commodities to own due to its “safe investment” tag. Because Gold is a staple of global economy, it is regarded as a low risk-high return asset in times of duress. However, investment in Gold does not mean stacking up piles of Gold bars in your house.    How Gold ETF Works?Nowadays, the simplest form of investment in Gold is ETF, exchange traded funds. Without owning a physical Gold asset, investors can simply invest in Gold ETF allowing them to profit from the positive movement of Gold price. There are many types of Gold ETF that may attract potential investors. As such, Gold ETF can also take the form of derivative contract, futures or gold-related index. There are also gold ETF that derive their prices from the Gold assets held in a trust. Similarly, there are specific gold ETF that track companies in the gold industry. As an example of a Gold ETF, consider investing in GLD, the SPDR Gold Share ETF. The SPDR Gold Share ETF is perhaps one of the most popular ETFs, which closely mimics the performance of the Gold prices allowing investors to reap the benefits of owning Gold without buying Gold bars and related assets. Why Buy Gold ETF?One of the main advantages of buying an ETF Gold is the exposure and simplicity of the asset class. For instance, if investors wanted to buy shares of Gold mining companies, owning a Gold ETF tailored towards such mining companies will offer full exposure to the Gold assets. In addition, investors do not have to worry about the excessive commissions and micro-economic impact on the shares of each individual gold mining company. Besides, there are tax advantages of the ETF because tax on profits are deferred until the sale of the ETF. Considering that Gold ETF do not have large commissions, tax on the final sale of the ETF is a very minor price to pay compared to the tax on other popular investment vehicles such as stocks, mutual funds and hedge funds etc.   Strategies for Trading GoldGold is one of the safest investments, therefore it is logical to use Gold ETF in a portfolio because it acts as an automatic hedge to the price of US Dollar. As the price of US Dollar decrease, Gold price is likely to increase. In fact, rise in US Dollar does not affect Gold prices because Gold is a universal benchmark that is not correlated with wild swings in the Forex economy. Selling Gold ETF can also be used to protect against the Gold Price if investors have major investments in a country that has Gold as a major source of income. Actually, Gold ETF options can also act as one of the safest investment strategies to balance any investment portfolio.          Tweet        Recent Posts What Is An ETF And How Are They Different From Mutual Funds? Major Oil ETFs You Should Be Considering For Your Portfolio How To Properly Invest In An Gold ETF? What Are The Benefits Top 3 Stock ETFs That Millennials Absolutely Love The Must Have ETF Tips and Advice For High Yielding ResultsCategoriesDividend ETFEnergy ETFETF TipsETFs InvestingGold ETFsOil ETFsStock ETFsWhat Is A ETF       

